# ==============================================================================
# Cloud Security Review Board (CSRB) Agent — Multi-Provider Configuration Template
# ==============================================================================
# Copy this file to a new file named '.env' in this same directory and configure
# it according to your preferred model provider.
#
# Because we use the standard OpenAI Python SDK, we can connect to any provider 
# that exposes an OpenAI-compatible API endpoint by setting the base URL, key, 
# and target model.

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Standard OpenAI Cloud API
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-yourActualOpenAiKeyHere
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini  # (Recommended) Or gpt-4o
# OPENAI_API_BASE=          # Keep empty or commented out for default OpenAI Cloud

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Google Gemini API (via OpenAI compatibility layer)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get your key at: https://aistudio.google.com/
#
# OPENAI_API_BASE=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/
# OPENAI_API_KEY=AIzaSyYourGeminiApiKeyHere
# OPENAI_MODEL=gemini-1.5-flash  # Or gemini-2.5-flash

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Groq Cloud API (High-speed Llama models)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get your key at: https://console.groq.com/
#
# OPENAI_API_BASE=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=gsk_YOUR_GROQ_API_KEY_HERE
# OPENAI_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile  # Or llama3-8b-8192

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. xAI Grok API
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get your key at: https://console.x.ai/
#
# OPENAI_API_BASE=https://api.x.ai/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=xai-yourGrokApiKeyHere
# OPENAI_MODEL=grok-2-1212

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. Nvidia NIM (Hosted Nvidia models)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get your key at: https://build.nvidia.com/
#
# OPENAI_API_BASE=https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=nvapi-yourNvidiaNimKeyHere
# OPENAI_MODEL=meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. OpenRouter (Gateway to Anthropic Claude, etc.)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get your key at: https://openrouter.ai/
#
# OPENAI_API_BASE=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-yourOpenRouterKeyHere
# OPENAI_MODEL=anthropic/claude-3-haiku

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. Local LM Studio Configuration
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_BASE=http://localhost:1234/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=lm-studio  # Placeholder value required by the SDK client
# OPENAI_MODEL=model-identifier-loaded-in-lm-studio

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. Local Ollama Configuration
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_BASE=http://localhost:11434/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=ollama  # Placeholder value required by the SDK client
# OPENAI_MODEL=llama3

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Active Configuration (uncomment ONE provider block above and fill in your key)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=YOUR_API_KEY_HERE
# OPENAI_MODEL=YOUR_MODEL_NAME_HERE
# OPENAI_API_BASE=YOUR_BASE_URL_HERE_OR_LEAVE_BLANK_FOR_OPENAI
